@startuml gcba-iris_iris
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #ffffff
  BorderColor black
  Style roundrect
}
left to right direction

actor "IoT Device" as Device

rectangle "Dock" as Dock #palegreen {
}

rectangle "Dispatcher" as Dispatcher #lightsteelblue {
}

rectangle "Hook (Input)" as InputHook #lightyellow
rectangle "Hook (Output)" as OutputHook #lightyellow

rectangle "Handler" as Handler #mistyrose

rectangle "Thread Pool" as ThreadPool #aliceblue

' ========== Connections ==========
Device --> Dock : sends message\n(protocol specific)

Dock --> Dispatcher : parsed message object

Dispatcher --> InputHook : pre-processing
InputHook --> Dispatcher 

Dispatcher --> Handler : process message
Handler --> Dispatcher : response (optional)

Dispatcher --> OutputHook : post-processing
OutputHook --> Dispatcher

Dispatcher --> ThreadPool : execute flow
ThreadPool --> Dispatcher : completed job

Dispatcher --> Dock : encoded response (if any)
Dock --> Device : sends response

' Event communication
Dispatcher -[hidden]right- Dispatcher
note on link: uses events for\ninter-component\ncommunication
@enduml